        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 4:16PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 416 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles north of Hasty, or 22 miles northwest of Lamar, moving south at
25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hasty, McClave, John Martin Reservoir, and Caddoa.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
